## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':

inflation_data <- read_excel("~/Downloads/CPI - Dataset No Description.xlsx")
inflation_data <- inflation_data %>%
  select(-HALF1, -HALF2)

inflation_data$Annual_Inflation <- rowMeans(inflation_data[, 2:13], na.rm = TRUE)

inflation_ts <- ts(as.numeric(t(inflation_data[, 2:13])), start = c(2014, 1), frequency = 12)

fedfunds_data <- read.csv("~/Downloads/FEDFUNDS.csv")
fedfunds_data$DATE <- as.Date(fedfunds_data$DATE)
fedfunds_data$Year <- as.numeric(format(fedfunds_data$DATE, "%Y"))
fedfunds_filtered <- fedfunds_data %>%
  filter(Year >= 2014 & Year <= 2024) %>%
  group_by(Year) %>%
  summarize(FedFunds_Rate = mean(FEDFUNDS, na.rm = TRUE))

merged_data <- inflation_data %>%
  inner_join(fedfunds_filtered, by = "Year")
plot(inflation_ts, main = "Inflation Time Series", ylab = "Inflation", xlab = "Year")

hist(inflation_data$Annual_Inflation, main = "Histogram of Annual Inflation", 
     xlab = "Inflation", breaks = 10)

boxplot(inflation_data$Annual_Inflation, main = "Boxplot of Annual Inflation", ylab = "Inflation")

tsdisplay(inflation_ts, main = "ACF and PACF for Inflation")

mult_decomp <- decompose(inflation_ts, type = "multiplicative")
add_decomp <- decompose(inflation_ts, type = "additive")
plot(mult_decomp)

plot(add_decomp)

seasonal_adjusted <- seasadj(mult_decomp)
plot(inflation_ts)
lines(seasonal_adjusted, col = "red")

naive_model <- naive(inflation_ts, h = 12)
plot(forecast(naive_model), main = "Naive Model Forecast")

naive_accuracy <- accuracy(naive_model)
print(naive_accuracy)
##                     ME    RMSE      MAE       MPE      MAPE      MASE      ACF1
## Training set 0.6368504 1.15389 0.874063 0.2329328 0.3274991 0.1135632 0.5759415
ets_model <- ets(inflation_ts)
## Warning in ets(inflation_ts): Missing values encountered. Using longest
## contiguous portion of time series
ets_forecast <- forecast(ets_model, h = 12)
plot(ets_forecast, main = "ETS Forecast")

ets_accuracy <- accuracy(ets_forecast)
print(ets_accuracy)
##                      ME      RMSE       MAE        MPE     MAPE       MASE
## Training set 0.02598797 0.7028751 0.5309777 0.01219424 0.200057 0.06898764
##                   ACF1
## Training set 0.3697082
inflation_ts <- na.omit(inflation_ts)
hw_model <- HoltWinters(inflation_ts)
plot(hw_model, main = "Holt-Winters Model")

hw_forecast <- forecast(hw_model, h = 12)
plot(hw_forecast, main = "Holt-Winters Forecast")

hw_accuracy <- accuracy(hw_forecast)
print(hw_accuracy)
##                      ME      RMSE       MAE        MPE      MAPE       MASE
## Training set 0.01886934 0.9475624 0.7201522 0.01057948 0.2707807 0.09356628
##                   ACF1
## Training set 0.3553921
hw_residuals <- residuals(hw_model)
tsdisplay(hw_residuals, main = "Holt-Winters Residual Diagnostics")

arima_model <- auto.arima(inflation_ts)
arima_forecast <- forecast(arima_model, h = 12)
plot(arima_forecast)

arima_accuracy <- accuracy(arima_forecast)
arima_residuals <- residuals(arima_model)
tsdisplay(arima_residuals, main = "ARIMA Residual")

regression_model <- lm(Annual_Inflation ~ FedFunds_Rate, data = merged_data)
regression_residuals <- residuals(regression_model)
summary(regression_model)
